====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{senseid|en|character}} {{lb|en|orthography}} The text character '''[[’]]''', which serves as a [[punctuation]] mark in various languages and as a [[diacritical mark]] in certain rare contexts.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2021|author=Claire Cock-Starkey|title=Hyphens & Hashtags|publisher=Bodleian Library|page=30|passage=Since its inception the '''apostrophe''' has been a controversial piece of punctuation.}}
=====Usage notes=====
In English, the apostrophe is used to mark the [[possessive]] (e.g., “my friend’s wife”), and to show the [[omission]] of letters (e.g., “my friend’s angry”) or of numbers (e.g., "during the 1960s and ’70s").

